/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/sturdy_find_and_validate_t02/rounds/round_1/merge_stdout.log:1:{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Balancer LP collateral is priced from a transient, callback-visible pool state","locations":["FlawVerifier.sol:320","FlawVerifier.sol:322","FlawVerifier.sol:324","FlawVerifier.sol:385","Contract.sol:288","Contract.sol:291","Contract.sol:302"],"claim":"The reproduced exploit reads `STURDY_ORACLE.getAssetPrice(CB_STETH_STABLE)` immediately before `BALANCER.exitPool`, again from the ETH-receiving `receive()` callback that fires while `exitPool` is still executing, and again after the exit completes. `FlawVerifier.notifyPrices` then marks `hypothesisValidated = duringPrice > beforePrice && duringPrice > afterPrice`, showing that the oracle returns a temporarily inflated B-stETH-STABLE price during Balancer exit reentrancy rather than a stable post-state valuation.","impact":"Any lending action that trusts this LP price for health-factor or collateral checks can be flash-manipulated inside one transaction. An attacker can transiently overvalue B-stETH-STABLE collateral, pass checks they should fail, and leave the protocol undercollateralized once the Balancer pool state normalizes, causing lender bad debt or insolvency.","paths":["Flash-loan WSTETH/WETH, join the Balancer B-stETH-STABLE pool, deposit BPT as collateral, then call `BALANCER.exitPool(...)` and use the callback window where `getAssetPrice(CB_STETH_STABLE)` is inflated to perform otherwise-disallowed credit actions."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Collateral can be disabled under the manipulated LP price and withdrawn after normalization","locations":["FlawVerifier.sol:328","FlawVerifier.sol:385","FlawVerifier.sol:386","Contract.sol:306","Contract.sol:318"],"claim":"The exploit leg uses the `exitPool` callback to call `LENDING_POOL.setUserUseReserveAsCollateral(CSTECRV, false)` exactly while the manipulated B-stETH-STABLE oracle price is elevated, then later calls `CONVEX_CURVE_LP_VAULT.withdrawCollateral(address(STECRV), 1_000 ether, ...)` after the price has already fallen back. This demonstrates that collateral-disable / withdraw eligibility is enforced against an instantaneous, callback-manipulable health check instead of a manipulation-resistant valuation.","impact":"A borrower can remove legitimate supporting collateral while the protocol temporarily overestimates another collateral asset, keep the borrowed funds, and leave the account liquidatable or underwater once prices normalize. The demonstrated path directly creates bad debt and lets the attacker realize value by liquidating the weakened position and reclaiming collateral.","paths":["Deposit `STECRV` and B-stETH-STABLE as collateral, borrow WETH, start `BALANCER.exitPool(...)`, disable `STECRV` as collateral from the callback while BPT is overpriced, wait for the oracle to normalize, then withdraw `STECRV` and liquidate the now-undercollateralized account."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[]}
